function.arguments: {"agentId":"summarizer_agent","agentInput":"{\"data\":\"War and Peace is a historical novel by Leo Tolstoy, first published in 1869. It is set during the Napoleonic Wars and follows the lives of several aristocratic families in Russia, particularly focusing on Pierre Bezukhov, Prince Andrei Bolkonsky, and Natasha Rostova. The novel explores themes of fate, free will, and the nature of history, intertwining personal stories with historical events. It delves into the impact of war on society and individuals, illustrating the struggles of love, loss, and the search for meaning in a tumultuous world. The narrative is rich with philosophical reflections and character development, ultimately portraying the complexity of human experience against the backdrop of a changing world.\"}"}
